# Example configuration for using Cloudflare API Proxy
#
# This shows how to configure trainboard to use the Cloudflare Worker proxy
# instead of calling the ODPT API directly.
#
# Benefits of using the proxy:
# - API key is never exposed in browser
# - Improved performance with edge caching
# - Better security and rate limiting
#
# After deploying the Cloudflare Worker (see README.md):
# 1. Copy this file to the project root as config.json
# 2. Update API_BASE_URL with your worker URL
# 3. Remove ODPT_API_KEY (proxy handles it securely)
#
# Example config.json using proxy:

{
  "API_BASE_URL": "https://odpt-api-proxy.YOUR-SUBDOMAIN.workers.dev/",
  "DEFAULT_RAILWAY": "odpt.Railway:Tokyu.Toyoko",
  "DEFAULT_STATION_NAME": "武蔵小杉 (TY11)"
}

# Notes:
# - Replace YOUR-SUBDOMAIN with your actual Cloudflare Workers subdomain
# - The trailing slash in API_BASE_URL is required
# - No ODPT_API_KEY needed - the worker handles authentication
# - The worker adds the API key server-side before proxying to ODPT
